## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone & create virtual environment

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd jobbhub
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate        # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Configure environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` with your values:

```env
SECRET_KEY=your-very-secret-key-here
DEBUG=True
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1

DB_NAME=jobbhub_db
DB_USER=jobbhub_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
```

### 4. Set up MySQL database

```sql
CREATE DATABASE jobbhub_db CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
CREATE USER 'jobbhub_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'your_db_password';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON jobbhub_db.* TO 'jobbhub_user'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
```

### 5. Run migrations

```bash
python manage.py makemigrations accounts
python manage.py makemigrations jobs
python manage.py makemigrations applications
python manage.py makemigrations subscriptions
python manage.py migrate
```

### 6. Load initial data fixtures

```bash
python manage.py loaddata fixtures/categories.json
python manage.py loaddata fixtures/plans.json
```

### 7. Create superuser

```bash
python manage.py createsuperuser
```

### 8. Collect static files (production)

```bash
python manage.py collectstatic
```

### 9. Run development server

```bash
python manage.py runserver
```

Visit **http://127.0.0.1:8000/** to see the app.

