## Security Notes

- All sensitive credentials live in `.env` (never commit this file)
- CSRF protection is enabled on all forms
- File uploads are validated: PDF only, max 5 MB
- Role decorators (`@employer_required`, `@jobseeker_required`) protect all sensitive views
- `@login_required` is applied to all authenticated routes

---

## Honeypot Protection

This project uses **two layers** of honeypot security:

### 1. Form Honeypot вЂ” `django-honeypot`

An invisible field named `phonenumber` is injected into every public form (register, login, apply, post job, edit job, profile). Legitimate users never see or fill it. Bots that auto-fill all fields get blocked immediately and see a `400 Bad Request` page (`templates/honeypot/honeypot_error.html`).

**How it works:**
- `HONEYPOT_FIELD_NAME = 'phonenumber'` in `settings.py` вЂ” realistic name fools smarter bots
- `HoneypotMiddleware` in `MIDDLEWARE` covers all POST responses site-wide
- `@check_honeypot` decorator on individual views adds a second layer of explicit checking
- `{% render_honeypot_field %}` in each form template renders the hidden field (hidden via CSS, not `type="hidden"`, so bots can see it but humans can't)

**To change the field name** (recommended before going live):
```python
# settings.py
HONEYPOT_FIELD_NAME = 'your_new_field_name'  # update all templates too
```

### 2. Admin Honeypot вЂ” `django-admin-honeypot`

| URL | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `/admin/` | **Fake** login page вЂ” logs all intrusion attempts |
| `/secret-admin/` | **Real** Django admin panel |

Any bot or attacker who hits `/admin/` gets a convincing fake login page. Every attempt is logged to the database and visible in the real admin panel under **Admin Honeypot в†’ Login Attempts**.

**Before going live вЂ” change the secret admin path:**
```python
# jobbhub/urls.py
path('your-secret-path/', admin.site.urls),  # pick something unguessable
```

**View login attempts in admin:**
Go to `/secret-admin/` в†’ Login Attempts section to see all caught bots with IP address, username tried, and timestamp.

